INTERNATIONAL - Huawei has revealed its new lineup of P-Series flagship smartphones at a launch event in Paris.   The new smartphone range features the Huawei P20, P20 Pro, and P20 Lite. Huawei’s P20 series showcases bold new design features similar lookng to the iPhone X, including bezel-less, notched displays, and a triple-lens camera on the P20 Pro. Huawei said its new devices are designed to deliver professional photography features in a smartphone. The P20 series phones have high-resolution front cameras in addition to improved rear camera systems. The P20 Pro’s camera features 3x optical zoom, 5x hybrid zoom, and “best-in-class” 10x digital zoom. According to Huawei, The device’s camera also includes zero shutter lag and intelligent motion detection. The P20 and P20 Pro can also both shoot slow-motion video in 720p quality at up to 960 frames per second, matching the Samsung Galaxy S9, and there’s a 24MP f/2.0 camera on the front. “With the Huawei P20 and P20 Pro, anyone can take professional pictures on their smartphone,” said Huawei Consumer CEO Richard Yu. featured in both devices is Huawei’s Kirin 970 processor with integrated AI features which powers the devices and aids in processing images taken with its triple-lens camera. Both devices have a 24MP front-facing camera and will be available in four colours, said Huawei – Twilight, Pink Gold, Midnight Blue, and Black. Huawei said South Africa would be part of the initial launch wave for the Huawei P20 and P20 Pro. The P20 key Features:   The P20 Pro key features:   OS:             		Android 8.1Display:      	6.1-inch 1,080 x 2,240 AMOLEDProcessor:	    HiSilicon Kirin 970RAM:          		6GBStorage:  	   		128GB, microSD 256GBRear Camera: 	Triple-lens – 40MP, 20MP, 8MPFront Camera:		24MPBattery:			 4,000mAhConnectivity:			Bluetooth 4.2, 802.11ac Wi-Fi, USB Type-CNetwork:						LTEPrice:			R15,999 Additionally, The company also launched two new audio accessories – a pair of wireless earphones called FreeBuds 